Name: Rheolease® 2416
Short description: Rheolease® 2416 is a specialist mandrel release agent originally designed to work with acrylic rubber compounds, such as HT-ACM, Vamac and ACM. Key features include high viscosity, fast BOD and non-hazardous.
Description: Rheolease® 2416 is a specialist mandrel release agent originally designed to work with acrylic rubber compounds, such as HT-ACM, Vamac and ACM. Due to the chemistry of this synthetic polymer, wetting of mandrels is achieved and maintained after vulcanisation. This results in excellent lubricity both before and after curing. Rheolease® 2416 also has excellent biodegradability (>60% in 5 days).
Meta: accordion_0_accordion_content:
• HT – ACM
  • Vamac
  • ACM
  • CR
  • CM
  • FKM
Meta: accordion_1_accordion_content:
Benefits of Rheolease® 2416 include:

  • High Biodegradability (BOD)
  • Low Chemical Oxygen Demand (COD)
  • Non-hazardous
  • Excellent loading and release performance (pin and pull)
  • Reduced mandrel fouling
  • Water washable
  • Low cost
Meta: accordion_2_accordion_content:
Appearance = Pale yellow viscous liquid

Viscosity @ 40°C = 2000cPs

Viscosity @ 25°C = 4000cPs

pH (5% Aqueous) = 7.0
Meta: accordion_3_accordion_content:
Rheolease® 2416 is available in the following pack sizes:

  • 1000kg IBC
  • 2400lb IBC/tote
  • 200kg Drum
  • 20kg Keg
Meta: accordion_4_accordion_content:
The following alternatives to Rheolease® 2416 are available:

  • Rheolease® 2416LV - Lower Viscosity
  • Rheolease® 2416MV - Higher Viscosity
  • Rheolease® 2544G - Extrusion gel compatible with Rheolease® 2416.

We can also design bespoke solutions to meet your needs. Please contact us to arrange a consultation with one of our experts.
